summary_markdown: This table presents a comparative analysis of "Reality" versus "Objective" states, centered around the concept of "Brand Equity." In the current "Reality," customers are "Owned," implying a transactional or captive relationship, while competition is "Claimed," suggesting a focus on asserting market position. The "Objective" future state, however, envisions a shift towards customers being "Valued," indicating a move towards customer-centricity and relationship building. Concurrently, competition is to be "Desired," signifying a strategic aspiration to be the preferred choice in the market. This framework outlines a progression from a present, possession-based approach to a future, relationship-driven strategy aimed at enhancing Brand Equity.
